\subsection{Stem group}
\begin{definition}\label{group.stem_group}
\uses{group,group.center,group.commutator_subgroup,group.isoclinism}
A **stem group** is a {{KNOWL('group', 'group')}} $G$ whose {{KNOWL('group.center', 'center')}} is contained in its {{KNOWL('group.commutator_subgroup', 'commutator subgroup')}}.  Any group is {{KNOWL('group.isoclinism', 'isoclinic')}} to a stem group (not necessarily unique), and the order of a stem group divides the order of every other group in its isoclinism class.
\end{definition}


